This paper deals with link scheduling in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the physical interference model, which is related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The algorithm proposed in the paper is fully distributed, which suggests that it may fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with achieving stability in the network, which is related to control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm that maximizes throughput, which is related to optimization and algorithms, making cs.MA (Machine Learning) a possible category as well.
